-Download MBed Studio (IDE)
https://os.mbed.com/studio/
-Download Tera Terminal (Application to write output on terminal from LCP1768)
https://os.mbed.com/handbook/Windows-scerial-configuration

Programs are located in C:\Users\<username>\Mbed\Programs

#Instructions to build program
#config Program_Directory - likely unnecessary
> mbed new .
> mbed add mbed-os
#specify target device
> mbed target LPC1768
#specify toolchain
> mdbed toolchain ARM
#compile program
> mbed compile
#copy build image to device if named drive (D:)
> copy .\BUILD\LPC1768\ARM\<program name>.bin D:



---------------------
Organization
---------------------
./Bluetooth holds the source code to manage the wireless connection

./Temp_Sensor holds the source code to recieve analog data from the
temperature sensor and translate it to digital

./Encrypt holds the source code to secure the data transferred wirelessly

./Desktop holds the server program to receive temperature from sensor and display it to screen
install blueman bluetooth tool for linux - this is to pair devices without using pin
Fedora server
un : groot
pw : 1234
https://wiki.qt.io/Building_Qt_5_from_Git
configuration for Qt
../qt5/configure -developer-build -opensource -nomake examples -nomake tests -static -prefix /home/groot/Documents/qt5-build
getting runtime error that said it couldn't find fonts

Adding system fonts to Qt library with symbolic links
ln -snf /usr/share/fonts/dejavu-serif-fonts/ /home/groot/Documents/qt5-build/qtbase/lib/dejavu-serif
ln -snf /usr/share/fonts/dejavu-sans-mono-fonts/ /home/groot/Documents/qt5-build/qtbase/lib/dejavu-sans-mono
ln -snf /usr/share/fonts/ /home/groot/Documents/qt5-build/qtbase/lib/dejavu-sans

Serial Communicaton Notes
Make sure to run program as root

